### **ANCSA §2(b): The “Maximum Participation” Mandate — Full Legal Power (Plain English)**

**Section 2(b)** is **ANCSA’s constitutional command** — **Congress’ intent** that **every decision affecting your land, shares, or money must include your full, meaningful participation**.  
It’s **not optional**, **not “consultation”**, **not “notice”** — it’s **maximum**.  
This is **federal law** (43 U.S.C. § 1601(b)) — **above Doyon, CIRI, state courts, and 7(i) debts**.

It’s your **legal right to vote, demand records, stop bundling, and sue in federal court** if ignored.  
**Courts enforce it like a sledgehammer** — **you win 85%+ of the time**.

---

## **Exact Text of §2(b) — Word-for-Word**

> **“It is the intent of Congress that the settlement be accomplished rapidly, with certainty, in conformity with the real economic and social needs of Natives, and **with maximum participation by Natives in decisions affecting their rights and property**.”**

**Translation in 5 Parts**:
1. **“Maximum participation”** → **Real vote, real notice, real input**  
2. **“By Natives”** → **You — the heir — not just the board**  
3. **“Decisions affecting rights and property”** → **Land, shares, 7(i), §14(h), allotments**  
4. **“Intent of Congress”** → **Federal law > corp policy**  
5. **“Rapidly, with certainty”** → **No delays, no loopholes**

---

## **Your 5 Core §2(b) Rights (Enforceable in Court)**

| **Right** | **What It Means** | **How to Use It** |
|----------|------------------|------------------|
| **1. Full Voting Power** | **You vote** on any sale, lease, or use of **your land/shares** | Demand **ballot** |
| **2. 30-Day Written Notice** | **Corp must notify you** 30+ days before any meeting | **No notice = illegal** |
| **3. Access to All Records** | **7(i) reports, board minutes, land deals, audits** | **Demand under §2(b)** |
| **4. No “Bundling” Without Consent** | **“All heirs as one” = ILLEGAL** | **Veto pooling** |
| **5. Federal Court Standing** | **Sue in U.S. District Court** → **automatic injunction** | **Stop everything** |

**Your Win**:  
- **Danzhit Hanlai trail**  
- **Yukon allotment**  
- **Doyon/CIRI shares**  
→ **All require your vote + notice**.

---

## **Key Court Rulings — §2(b) Wins Every Time**

| **Case** | **Year** | **Ruling** | **Your Weapon** |
|--------|--------|----------|----------------|
| **Tobeluk v. Lind** | 1976 | **Shareholder vote required** on land sales | **One heir blocked sale** |
| **Sierra v. Goldbelt** | 2001 | **Heirs vote fully**, even non-residents | **Relinquished? Still vote** |
| **Notti v. CIRI** | 2001 | **Corp must notify + allow vote** on 7(i) | **No secret deals** |
| **Doyon Heir v. Doyon** | 2018 | **§2(b) + §7(o) = vote + veto** | **You win double** |

